article.headline: Southern Illinois 102, Tennessee State 62
article.story: COOKEVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Willie Jenkins had 32 points and six rebounds to lead Tennessee Tech to a 102-62 win over Virginia Intermont Tuesday night. Jenkins also had a team-high six rebounds for the Golden Eagles (1-1), who dominated with 54 percent shooting from the field. He was also a perfect 11-11 from the free throw line. Virginia Intermont (0-7) fell behind 49-30 by the half and trailed the rest of the way. Intermont was led with 20 points from Chris Wise, the team's only player in double digits. Tennessee Tech had three others score in double digits. Ben Jacobsen had 15 points, Derek Stribling had 14 points and Milone Clark added 10 points.
